      <h1 class="h4 mb-3">1. Load HET on the page</h1>
      <div class="tutorial-content mb-4">
        <p>The first thing to do is reference the HET javascript file on your page, and then initialize it with <code>HET.init()</code>.</p>
        <p>For components, <code>HET.init()</code> scans the page and mounts anything it recognizes. It also initializes HET's request enhancement behavior. Various configuration options can be passed into <code>HET.init()</code>, but we'll be sticking with the defaults for this tutorial.</p>
        <p>Reference documentation:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="reference/api#initconfig"><code>init(config)</code></a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

